ils: The exhibition takes place until November 16 at the SMAC Art Gallery, 1st Floor, De Wet Centre, 2 Church Street. For more information visit www.smacgallery.com or call 021 887 3607 A Thousand Things: Bulumko Mbete uses a combination of domestic and utilitarian textiles to visualise her thoughts on human knowledge and humankind’s sense of place. She makes alternative use of the materials to challenge the viewer’s experience of the textiles and as such encouraging them to discourage the act of assuming or stereotyping. Details: The exhibition takes place until November 23 at 99 Loop Gallery, 99 Loop Street, Cape Town City Centre. For more information visit www.99loop.co.za or call 021 422 3766 Buzzart 19: With Christmas on the way, this fair brings local handmade product designers of soft furnishings, jewellery, art, ceramics, toys and confectionaries together for early Christmas shopping. Details: The show takes place on November 14 at the KZNSA Gallery, 166 Bulwer Road Glenwood. For more information visit www.kznsagallery.co.za or call 031 277 1705 Flipside: Directed by Yuhl Headman, this stage play takes a look at the life of those who find themselves displaced in the ever changing but staying the same nature of the world. Details: The show will be staged until November 17 at the South African State Theatre, 320 Pretorius Street, Pretoria Central. Tickets cost R100 and can be purchased from www.webtickets.co.za. For more information visit www.statetheatre.co.za or call 012 392 400 Improv play offs: Old versus new: Come witness theatre players of the Market Lab go up against the current Market Lab students in a big to compare and contrast old and new theatre practices. Details: The show takes place on November 15 at the Market Theatre, 56 Margaret Mcingana Street (previously Wolhuter). Tickets cost R50 and can be purchased from www.webtickets.co.za. For more information visit www.markettheatre.co.za or call 011 832 1641 Charlie and the Chocolate Factory: Bring the whole family out to watch the reenactment of a classic Roald Dahl book and film on stage. Alongside his grandfather, Charlie Bucket goes on an adventure that transforms his life of lack into one of wonders. Details: The show is being staged until December 22 at the National Children’s Theatre, Junction Avenue Parktown. Tickets cost R80 to R130. For more information or to book tickets visit www.nationalchildrenstheatre.org.za or call 011 484 1584 Blue Note Records: Beyond The Notes: Directed by Sophie Huber this music documentary traces the story behind the emergence of pioneering and prolific jazz record label, Blue Note Records. Details: The film will be screened on November 14 at The Bioscope, 286 Fox Street. Tickets cost R60 to R110 and can be purchased from tixsa.co.za. For more information visit www.thebioscope.co.za or call 087 830 0445